org.hibernate.graph

Class GraphParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.graph.GraphParser

  • public final class GraphParser
extends Object
    Parser for string representations of JPA EntityGraph (RootGraph) and Subgraph (SubGraph), using a simple syntax defined by the `graph.g` Antlr grammar.

    The parse(java.lang.Class<T>, java.lang.CharSequence, javax.persistence.EntityManager) methods all create a root EntityGraph based on the passed entity class and parse the graph string into that root graph.

    The parseInto(org.hibernate.graph.Graph<T>, java.lang.CharSequence, javax.persistence.EntityManager) methods parse the graph string into a passed graph, which may be a sub-graph

    Multiple graphs made for the same entity type can be merged. See EntityGraphs.merge(javax.persistence.EntityManager, java.lang.Class<T>, javax.persistence.EntityGraph<T>...).
